        "timestamp": "2018-07-24 14:05:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(7 comments)\n\nBesides the comments on individual files, I have a general question of whether or not this is needed.  SystemPersistence already provides a mechanism to look up Properties by feature name.  In addition, the PropertyConfiguration class provides automatic loading & type verification of property values, from a Properties object, directed by @Property annotations.  An example of its use can be found in PoolingProperties.",
